properties.description:
Over the past week, the water levels on the area rivers remain high; 
tobacco leaves have been topped & remaining crop is yellowing; soy continues to do well; corn continues to dry on the stalks; fields remain difficult, if not impossible to work due to moisture levels;
cooler temperatures and shorter days have started the red maple leaves to turn & the crepe myrtle leaves to drop; 
wild turkeys are plentiful ( out of hunting season )
fewer hummingbirds remain


